    en: "New York Civil Practice Law and Rules Article 63 (Sections 6301-6330) gives civil litigants the tools to get emergency and pendente lite relief before a case is decided on the merits. A Temporary Restraining Order (TRO) under CPLR 6313 can issue ex parte (without the opposing party present) for immediate and irreparable harm. A Preliminary Injunction (PI) under CPLR 6301 preserves the status quo through trial after notice and an opportunity to be heard. A plaintiff must show (1) likelihood of success on the merits, (2) irreparable injury absent relief, and (3) balance of equities favors relief. The court may require an undertaking (bond) under CPLR 6312 to cover damages if the injunction is later found wrongful. These are not the same as an order of protection in domestic violence cases (FCA/CPL)."
